The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Saturday, October 04, 2003 				 6 die in attack
																								Karachi, Oct. 3 (Reuters): Gunmen attacked a bus carrying Shia worshippers in the Pakistani port city of Karachi today, killing six people and wounding eight, police said.																								Two or three gunmen riding a motorcycle opened fire with automatic weapons on a government bus carrying the worshippers to Friday prayers, Tariq Jameel, a deputy inspector general of police, said. Ambulance workers and doctors said five people died on the spot and a sixth died later in hospital.																								Most victims were employees of Pakistans Space amp; Upper Atmospheric Research Commission, using a company bus. 
